<br>
PBAoE are the only spells that allow a nearly unlimited number of creatures to be hit with one blast.  And theres been case after case of players shooting up levels incredibly fast because of it.  So far it's THE fastest way to XP, bar none.  And up til the recent XP changes, it blew every other means out of the water.<br>
<br>
Given that only a few classes are apt to it, and that we'd be highly offended by nerfing the number of creatures we can affect with the blast, verant simply decided not to support it much anymore.<br>
<br>
Thats a far easier solution after all then going to every zone where it may become a problem and inserting mobs with MR or changing around circumstances to make it harder to PBAOE.  They simply get it at its source.<br>
<br>
So thats why we don't get any new ones, to all the people that have been wondering.<br>
<br>
It begs the question though.   What use were they in the first place?   I can only assume they were some sort of suicide spell intentionally.. When mobs got too close to the caster and he thought he was going down anyway.  To blast a few that were already beating on him.  (hence the short casting times..)   If this was the intent, it was very ill concieved, as people tend to prefer to live for one, and thus won't want to aggrivate an already bad situation.  And two, that measily 1000 damage at 60th level for wizards (the best of the bunch) isn't likely to kill anything you'll be fighting at that level, or even wound them terribly.<br>
<br>
It is possible they will make a comeback.  Just recently in an AoE group I noticed my friend in a good DN group was earning about 2/3rds the XP I was for the same amount of time spent.  Granted the AoE group was getting poor pulls and the other group was doing very well.  But for a non AoE group, thats still very impressive.   Long story short, the new XP changes can make enough of a difference to close the gap.  And if the gap gets closed enough it's possible we'll see AoE spells come back in more limited form.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't hold your breath though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showPrevMessage?topicID=54.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showNextMessage?topicID=54.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.threadControl?topicID=54.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=54.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=54.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<option value="themagicianstowerspells">Spells<option value="themagicianstowerequipmentandquests">Quests<option value="themagicianstowerfrm28">Equipment<option value="themagicianstowerfrm29">Magician Pets<option value="themagicianstowerfrm30">Magician Skills<option value="themagicianstowerthelibrary">The L